{
  "text": "Sirs, Increased serum prolactin (PRL) levels have been demonstrated in several autoimmune diseases including polymyositis (PM) and systemic sclerosis (SSc) [CITATION_1] [2] [3] . PRL is produced by the lactotrophs of the pituitary gland, but the immune cells can produce PRL as well, and PRL acts as a cytokine with role in B, T, and dendritic cell maturation [CITATION_2] . Czuwara-Ladykowska et al.",
